---
import ProjectCard from "../../components/rfc/ProjectCard.astro";
import Layout from "../../layouts/Projects.astro";
---

<Layout title="Projects" description="Projects">
  <a
    class="hover:underline px-4 py-2 border border-gray-200 bg-gray-100 rounded-md"
    href="/">go back</a
  >
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold my-8 text-center">Projects</h1>

  <ProjectCard
    title="Logic Fed Scene Randomizer"
    link="/projects/lfsr"
    date="November 2025"
  >
    Logic Fed Scene Randomizer is a PCB art piece that illustrates how an LFSR
    works. A Linear Feedback Shift Register is a circuit capable of generating a
    sequence of random numbers from a starting non-zero value.
  </ProjectCard>
  <ProjectCard
    title="TinkerPod"
    link="/projects/tinker-pod"
    date="February 2025"
  >
    The TinkerPod is an Open-Source hardware platform designed to appeal to
    makers, creative coders, and designers by providing a hackable and
    customizable hardware.
  </ProjectCard>
  <ProjectCard
    title="CTRL Space"
    link="/projects/ctrl-space"
    date="November 2024"
  >
    An interactive art installation featuring three large mechanical eyes that
    follow visitors, bringing Michel Foucault's theory of the Panopticon into a
    contemporary context.
  </ProjectCard>
  <ProjectCard title="The Grid" link="/projects/the-grid" date="October 2023">
    A p5js-based audio-visual installation where phones become instruments in an
    E Minor pentatonic scale, with microphone input triggering visual feedback.
  </ProjectCard>
  <ProjectCard
    title="Colorful Delivery"
    link="/projects/colorful-delivery"
    date="2022"
  >
    A creative tool that utilizes a given hash value to create a captivating
    color matrix, with potential applications in data visualization.
  </ProjectCard>
  <ProjectCard
    title="Arduino LMiC adaptation to LoRaWAN v1.1"
    link="/projects/arduino-lmic-lorawan"
    date="2020"
  >
    Adaptation of the Arduino LMiC library to comply with LoRaWAN v1.1
    specification for A and C devices, incorporating enhanced security features.
  </ProjectCard>
</Layout>
